The Herald Sports Reporter
THE late former Premier Soccer League chief executive officer Chris Sambo, who died in Harare last night, will be buried tomorrow at Greendale Cemetery. Close family friend and Sambo’s long time football ally, Francis Zimunya, confirmed the funeral arrangements. “Please take note that our dear father, brother, friend and colleague, the late football icon Mr. Chris Sambo will be buried at 1100 hours, Friday 31st July, at Greendale Cemetery,” said Zimunya.